FBIS3-52654 "drnes004dd_94008" FBIS-NES-94-004 Document Type:Daily Report 6 Jan 1994 Palestinian Affairs Hurd Promises Funds for Autonomy TA0501180694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 5 Jan 94 TA0501180694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd promised during a tour of the Gaza Strip today that the British would assist in the establishment of the autonomy in the West Bank and Gaza Strip and would immediately grant 20 million pounds sterling to the Palestinians and another 70 million pounds sterling in another two years. Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that during the tour, Hurd conferred with Zakariya al-Agha, Fatah leader of the Gaza Strip, and Mansur al-Shawwa, a leading Palestinian in the strip.
